Dear Hiring Team,

I am writing to apply for the *FileNet SharePoint Integration Developer* role with *Maagsoft*. I bring experience building enterprise backend systems in *Java*, *Spring Boot*, and *RESTful APIs*, along with hands-on work in *documents and metadata* workflows, operational support, and release automation. My graduate training in Computer Science from Pace University and my production experience across Sperse and Qualitest give me the technical depth this position demands.

At Qualitest, I designed a cloud-agnostic storage service in *Java* and *Spring Boot* that normalized *documents and metadata* in *PostgreSQL* and exposed *RESTful APIs* across *Google Cloud Storage*, *S3*, and *MinIO*. That work maps directly to *IBM FileNet* to *SharePoint* *migration utilities*: preserving metadata fidelity, handling file movement reliably, and keeping enterprise application integrations predictable. I also orchestrated long-running jobs with *AWS Step Functions*, reducing *AWS Lambda* timeouts and improving error recovery across *100K+* weekly executions, which is the same kind of operational discipline needed to apply *WebSphere* *fix packs* on schedule and keep supporting systems stable. My experience optimizing PostgreSQL and surfacing results through React dashboards also translates to investigating and resolving *ServiceNow* incidents and *service requests* with clear root-cause analysis and fast handoff.

At Sperse, I built a multi-agent CRM platform in *Python*, *LangGraph*, *LangChain*, and *FastAPI* with *RESTful APIs* for internal integrations, and I engineered a production *MCP* server over a multi-tenant *.NET framework* backend with Pydantic validation and OpenTelemetry instrumentation. I also built trace-driven eval suites and *GitHub Actions* *CI/CD* gates that replay real conversations, score latency and tool-call accuracy, and prevent unsafe changes from reaching production. That combination of specification-driven delivery, operational rigor, and clear technical communication fits the work of designing functional and technical specifications for enterprise applications and supporting the team through production issues.

Maagsoft’s mission to bridge the gap between vision and reality with *cutting-edge technology solutions* and its emphasis on *Quality*, *Integrity*, and *Innovation* resonate strongly with how I work. I would value the opportunity to help Maagsoft deliver on that mission by building reliable integration utilities, maintaining platform stability, and contributing to the team’s success with disciplined execution and clear documentation.

I would welcome the opportunity to discuss how my background aligns with your team and its mission. I can be reached at #ph or #eml. Thank you for your time and consideration.

